"The user browses View 1 at the [Overview] level and learns about the overall distribution of enrollments across all courses in the database. Next, the user selects specific courses of interest in View 1, affecting Views 2, 3, 4, and 5 at the [Exploration and Detail] levels. In View 2, the user discovers patterns between course perceived difficulty and enrollments using a heat map. In View 3, they analyze enrollment distribution across departments via a stacked bar chart, and in View 4, they explore temporal enrollment trends using a scatter plot of days and hours. Finally, in View 5, the user studies the effect of credit hours on course popularity using detailed box plots."